A)How to compile and run rosenbrock demo with ifort in Linux
option 1) use makefile.rosenbrock_ifort
to compile using makefile with ifort
  1) make -f makefile.rosenbrock_ifort
  2) ./rosenbrock_demo.exe
to remove intermediate files
  1) make -f makefile.rosenbrock_ifort clean

option 2) automatically generate batch file for compilng rosenbrock demo
make -f makefile.rosenbrock_ifort clean
make -f makefile.rosenbrock_ifort -n >rosenbrock_ifort.bat
chmod +x rosenbrock_ifort.bat
./rosenbrock_ifort.bat
./rosenbrock_demo.exe

B)How to compile and run rosenbrock demo with ifort in Windows
option 1) use rosenbrock_ifort.bat
option 2) use VS+IVF

C)How to compile and run rosenbrock demo with gfortran in Linux
option 1) use makefile.rosenbrock_gfortran
to compile and run using makefile with gfortran
  1) make -f makefile.rosenbrock_gfortran
  2) ./rosenbrock_demo.exe
to remove intermediate files
  1) make -f makefile.rosenbrock_gfortran clean

option 2) automatically generate batch file for compilng rosenbrock demo
make -f makefile.rosenbrock_gfortran clean
make -f makefile.rosenbrock_gfortran -n >rosenbrock_gfortran.bat
chmod +x rosenbrock_gfortran.bat
./rosenbrock_gfortran.bat
./rosenbrock_demo.exe

D)How to compile and run rosenbrock demo with gfortran in Windows
option 1) use rosenbrock_gfortran.bat
option 2) use gfortran command prompt